6:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both CodeGPT and Qodo share a solid foundation of core features including Debugging, Multi Language, Ide Integration, Chat. Where CodeGPT pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Autocomplete and Code Generation, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. On the other hand, Qodo uniquely offers Code Review and Test Generation, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, CodeGPT holds an overall score of 6/10 and an ease of use score of 7/10, while Qodo scores 7/10 overall and 7/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, CodeGPT offers a more budget-friendly entry point at $9.99/mo, compared to Qodo's starting price of $19/mo. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. CodeGPT's free tier and Qodo's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
