a:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. CodeGPT is best suited for developers wanting LLM flexibility, VS Code users, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Qodo, meanwhile, shines for quality focused development teams, automated test generation, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2023, CodeGPT describes itself as \"Connect any AI model to your code editor.\" Qodo, established in 2022, positions itself as \"AI-powered code integrity and test generation.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
b:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Qodo** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (7.0 vs 6.0), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean CodeGPT is a poor choice — far from it. CodeGPT excels in its own right, particularly for developers wanting LLM flexibility and VS Code users.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value strong test generation, go with Qodo. If multiple llm provider support matters more to you, CodeGPT is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
